\label{L- Hamiltonian cycles} 
The Moebius ladder $L$ contains precisely five Hamiltonian graphs:
\begin{enumerate}
\item A unique cycle without rungs
\item Four cycles having a pair of missing consecutive rungs
\end{enumerate}
By consecutive rung, we mean rungs connected by two horizontal edges. Furthemore, the rungs in a Hamiltonian cycle in case 2 are at distance 3 (i.e., separated by a pair of paths consisting of three horizontal edges).

